With barely 50 days to the first Election Day on February 25, the Independent National Electoral Commission has expressed satisfaction with the turnout for Permanent Voters Cards collection across the country ahead of the 2023 election. Speaking on Friday during a television programme monitored by our correspondent, the INEC National Commissioner and Chairman of Information and Voter Education Committee, Festus Okoye, attributed the development to mobilization by leaders at different levels.
